  "prompt": "What happened when the Higgs Boson was discovered?",
  "response": "The discovery of the Higgs Boson was announced on July 4, 2012, by scientists at the Large Hadron Collider (LHC) at CERN in Geneva, Switzerland. Here are the key points:\n\n1. Confirmation of a long-predicted particle\n- The Higgs Boson was a missing piece in the Standard Model of particle physics\n- Theoretically predicted in 1964 by Peter Higgs and other physicists\n- Considered the \"God particle\" because it helps explain how other particles get mass\n\n2. Scientific significance\n- Proved the existence of the Higgs field, which gives mass to fundamental particles\n- Completed the Standard Model of particle physics\n- Validated decades of theoretical work by physicists\n\n3. Experimental process\n- Discovered through high-energy particle collisions at the LHC\n- Required analyzing enormous amounts of collision data\n- Scientists at ATLAS and CMS experiments independently confirmed the discovery\n\n4. Aftermath\n- Peter Higgs and Fran\u00e7ois Englert were awarded the Nobel Prize in Physics in 2013\n- Opened new avenues for understanding fundamental physics\n- Considered one of the most important scientific discoveries of the 21st century\n\nThe discovery was a major milestone in understanding the fundamental nature of matter and the universe.",
